WEBVTT

00:01.000 --> 00:03.298
The FX original series,
The Americans.

00:03.330 --> 00:05.628
The new season,
Wednesdays at 10:00 on FX.

00:08.370 --> 00:10.201
PREVIOUSLY ON
"THE AMERICANS"...

00:10.240 --> 00:11.969
THERE'S ONE MOVE WE COULD MAKE.
WE PUT A BUG IN GAAD'S OFFICE.

00:12.010 --> 00:13.307
Martha:
I'M IN LOVE WITH YOU,

00:13.340 --> 00:15.035
AND I WOULD DO
ANYTHING FOR YOU.

00:15.080 --> 00:17.844
Gabriel:
THAT STUDENT YOU FOLLOWED
MET WITH EUGENE VENTER

00:17.880 --> 00:19.211
FROM SOUTH AFRICAN
INTELLIGENCE.

00:19.250 --> 00:21.639
WHAT'S HE DOING
MEETING WITH AN UNDERGRADUATE?

00:21.680 --> 00:22.988
A LOT OF
THE ANTI-APARTHEID MOVEMENT

00:23.020 --> 00:24.715
IS CENTERED
ON COLLEGE CAMPUSES.

00:24.750 --> 00:26.149
Paige:
WHAT ARE WE DOING HERE, MOM?

00:26.190 --> 00:27.987
I HAD A GOOD FRIEND
WHO LIVED NEAR HERE.

00:28.020 --> 00:30.989
WE ALL WORKED TOGETHER
IN THE CIVIL RIGHTS MOVEMENT.

00:31.030 --> 00:32.998
YOUR PARENTS WERE
REAL ACT IVISTS.

00:33.030 --> 00:35.658
IF YOU TELL HER NOW,
THIS WILL ALL BLOW UP.

00:35.700 --> 00:38.396
BUT AT LEAST
SHE'LL KNOW WHO SHE IS.

00:38.430 --> 00:40.830
Gabriel: SHE HAS A SON.
SHE SAYS HE'S YOURS.

00:40.870 --> 00:43.236
HIS NAME IS MISHA.
HE'S 20 YEARS OLD.

00:43.270 --> 00:47.229
HE'S IN THE 345th
INDEPENDENT PARATROOP REGIMENT

00:47.280 --> 00:48.872
IN FAIZABAD.

00:53.280 --> 00:55.248
Reporter: ...AN UNKNOWN SOURCE
TOLD THE BBC

00:55.280 --> 00:57.009
THAT GOVERNMENT SOURCES
REAFFIRM ED

00:57.050 --> 01:00.019
THE SOVIET UNION'S COMMITMENT
TO THE WAR.

01:00.060 --> 01:01.857
AT A RECENT PARTY CONFERENCE,

01:01.890 --> 01:05.189
OFFICIALS CONDEMNED
THE UNITED STATES AND PAKISTAN

01:05.230 --> 01:07.596
FOR THE ONGOING STRIFE
IN AFGHANISTAN.

01:07.630 --> 01:10.895
MEANWHILE, THE UNITED NATIONS
CONTINUES TO SEEK AN END

01:10.930 --> 01:13.694
TO THE THREE-YEAR
MILITARY ENGAGEMENT THERE

01:13.740 --> 01:17.699
AS FIGHTING RAGES ON THE FRONTS
IN THE PANJSHIR VALLEY.

01:17.740 --> 01:19.776
THE SOVIET SPOKESMAN
REITERATED THE BELIEF

01:19.810 --> 01:23.871
THAT REVOLUTION IN AFGHANISTAN
COULD NOT BE TURNED BACK

01:23.910 --> 01:26.242
AND, THEREFORE,
ANY TROOP WITH DRAWAL

01:26.280 --> 01:27.872
WAS DEPENDENT ON DIRECT TALKS

01:27.920 --> 01:32.209
BETWEEN AFGHANISTAN,
PAKISTAN, AND IRAN.

01:32.260 --> 01:33.909
IN OTHER NEWS,

01:33.960 --> 01:36.087
BRUSH FIRES ARE RAGING
IN THE SOUTHERN STA--

01:36.130 --> 01:37.757
[ RADIO TURNS OFF ]

01:54.680 --> 01:55.908
HEY.

01:55.940 --> 01:57.441
WHAT ARE YOU READING?

02:00.950 --> 02:02.417
SCHOOL?

02:02.450 --> 02:04.281
NO.

02:05.820 --> 02:07.617
MOM TOLD ME
YOU GUYS DID SOME STUFF

02:07.660 --> 02:09.116
WITH THE CIVIL RIGHTS
MOVEMENT.

02:12.300 --> 02:13.927
YEAH, A LONG TIME AGO.

02:13.960 --> 02:16.099
NOT THAT LONG AGO.

02:16.130 --> 02:18.098
NOT REALLY.

02:18.130 --> 02:21.759
I MEAN, HOW OFTEN DO YOU SEE
A BLACK PERSON IN FALLS CHURCH?

02:21.800 --> 02:25.429
AND WHEN YOU DO,
PEOPLE GET TOTALLY FREAKED OUT.

02:25.470 --> 02:30.100
D.C. STILL HAS GHE'I'I'OS, DAD,
JUST LIKE IN THE 19605.

02:30.150 --> 02:33.779
YES.
YEAH, THAT'S TRUE.

02:33.820 --> 02:35.447
MOM TOOK ME
TO KENILWORTH.

02:35.480 --> 02:38.119
I MEAN, IT'S NOT LIKE
I DIDN'T KNOW

02:38.150 --> 02:39.981
THOSE SORTS OF NEIGHBORHOODS
EXISTED,

02:40.020 --> 02:43.524
BUT I'D JUST...
NEVER BEEN TO ONE BEFORE.

02:43.560 --> 02:45.778
MOM TOOK YOU
TO KENILWORTH?

02:45.830 --> 02:47.297
IT WASN'T SCARY.

02:47.330 --> 02:51.027
SOME OF IT WAS, BUT...

02:51.070 --> 02:54.335
IT WAS AMAZING --
WALKING WITH MOM

02:54.370 --> 02:56.531
AND SEEING PEOPLE
LIVE LIKE THAT,

02:56.570 --> 02:59.038
SO CLOSE
TO FALLS CHURCH.

02:59.070 --> 03:02.471
MOM TOLD ME
ABOUT YOUR FRIEND GREGORY.

03:02.510 --> 03:05.047
I CAN'T BELIEVE
YOU HAD A FRIEND

03:05.080 --> 03:08.049
WHO GOT KILLED
BY THE POLICE.

03:09.520 --> 03:11.818
YOU HAD A FRIEND
THAT GOT KILLED BY THE POLICE?

03:11.850 --> 03:13.989
HE WAS AN ACT IVIST.

03:14.020 --> 03:15.487
MOM AND DAD
WERE ACT IVISTS.

03:15.520 --> 03:16.657
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

03:16.690 --> 03:19.056
CIVIL RIGHTS ACT IVISTS.

03:19.090 --> 03:22.662
WHAT MADE YOU STOP BELIEVING
IN CHANGE, MAKING THINGS BETTER?

03:22.700 --> 03:25.828
I STILL BELIEVE
IN THOSE THINGS.

03:25.870 --> 03:28.668
YOU JUST GET OLDER.

03:28.700 --> 03:31.203
AND, UH...

03:31.240 --> 03:33.572
OTHER THINGS
BECOME IMPORTANT.

03:35.210 --> 03:38.407
AND YOU REALIZE THERE ARE A LOT
OF WAYS TO MAKE A DIFFERENCE.

03:38.450 --> 03:40.213
LET'S GO. COME ON.

03:40.250 --> 03:41.877
GOOD NIGHT.

04:00.070 --> 04:01.435
WHAT'S THAT?

04:01.470 --> 04:05.566
THE CENTRE ASKED
FOR WEEKLY UPDATES ON PAIGE.

04:20.090 --> 04:21.455
[ DRAWER OPENS ]

04:21.490 --> 04:23.219
[ ITEMS CLA'I'I'ERING ]

04:23.260 --> 04:25.251
WHAT ARE YOU LOOKING FOR?

04:25.290 --> 04:26.791
ASPIRIN.
[ OBJECT CLANKS ]

04:26.830 --> 04:29.560
[ CLA'ITERING CONTINUES ]

04:29.600 --> 04:32.068
THERE'S A NEW BOTTLE OF ASPIRIN
ON THE TOP SHELF.

04:32.100 --> 04:33.795
[ DRAWER SLAMS ]

04:35.600 --> 04:37.238
WHY WOULD YOU KEEP
AN EMPTY BOTTLE OF ASPIRIN?

04:37.270 --> 04:38.737
I DON'T SEE THE LOGIC.

04:38.770 --> 04:40.909
WELL, YOU FINISHED IT,
SO NEXT TIME, THROW IT OUT.

04:40.940 --> 04:44.273
PAIGE TOLD ME
ABOUT YOUR LITTLE FIELD TRIP.

04:48.950 --> 04:50.144
GOOD.

04:50.190 --> 04:52.249
YOU DIDN'T THINK
TO MENTION IT?

04:52.290 --> 04:54.952
I TOLD YOU
I WAS MOVING FORWARD WITH PAIGE.

04:54.990 --> 04:57.584
I DIDN'T THINK I NEEDED TO TELL
YOU EVERYTHING I DID EVERY DAY.

04:57.630 --> 04:59.825
IN THE FUTURE, I WOULD
APPRECIATE IT IF YOU
DIDN'T LIE TO ME.

04:59.860 --> 05:02.090
I DID NOT LIE TO YOU.
BECAUSE BELIEVE IT OR NOT,

05:02.130 --> 05:03.768
PAIGE DOES OCCASIONALLY
TALK TO ME.

05:03.800 --> 05:06.667
I DIDN'T LIE TO YOU.
I TOLD YOU I WAS MOVING FORWARD.

05:06.700 --> 05:08.463
IS THIS
HOW IT'S GONNA WORK?

05:10.970 --> 05:13.609
I MEAN, A-AM I --
AM I GONNA COME HOME ONE DAY

05:13.640 --> 05:18.475
AND...PAIGE WILL JUST TELL ME
THAT SHE KNOWS WHO WE ARE?

05:23.650 --> 05:25.686
I HONESTLY --
I DON'T KNOW.

06:18.210 --> 06:20.371
[ WATER SHUTS OFF ]

06:30.720 --> 06:32.756
GABRIEL TOLD ME
THEY'RE SENDING A GUY

06:32.790 --> 06:34.417
NAMED REUBEN NCGOBO.

06:34.460 --> 06:37.349
HE'LL BE HERE IN A FEW HOURS,
COMING IN FROM MOSCOW.

06:37.390 --> 06:39.381
MOSCOW?

06:39.430 --> 06:41.022
YEAH.

06:41.060 --> 06:44.359
HE'S AFRICAN NATIONAL CONGRESS,
TRAINING THERE.

06:44.400 --> 06:47.597
SO HE'S BAIT, HOPING VENTER
WILL COME AND KILL HIM.

06:47.640 --> 06:50.029
WELL,
HE'S NO ORDINARY BAIT.

06:50.070 --> 06:53.039
HE'S NUMBER 3 ON
SOUTH AFRICA'S MOST-WANTED LIST.

06:53.080 --> 06:55.878
AND WE TRUST HIM WHY --
'CAUSE HE'S A COMMUNIST?

06:55.910 --> 06:58.049
GABRIEL SAID THESE GUYS
GO BACK TO SOUTH AFRICA

06:58.080 --> 07:00.378
AND THEY DO WHAT THEY SAY
THEY'RE GONNA DO.

07:00.420 --> 07:02.217
A LOT OF THEM DIE.

07:02.250 --> 07:03.581
WE TRUST HIM.

07:05.450 --> 07:07.384
[ SPITS ]

07:07.420 --> 07:09.752
[ SHOWER WATER RUNNING ]

07:22.810 --> 07:24.607
WHAT WAS SHE LIKE?

07:26.110 --> 07:27.907
UH, WHAT DO YOU
WANT TO KNOW?

07:27.940 --> 07:30.249
OH, ANYTHING.

07:30.280 --> 07:33.147
NINA WAS...

07:33.180 --> 07:36.445
A GOOD PERSON,
STRAIGHTFORWARD.

07:36.490 --> 07:38.481
WE PUT HER
IN A COMPROMISED SITUATION,

07:38.520 --> 07:40.579
BUT SHE ROSE
TO THE OCCASION,

07:40.620 --> 07:42.827
DID WHAT WAS EXPECTED
OF HER.

07:42.860 --> 07:45.249
YEAH,
THE GUY I WAS RUNNING,

07:45.290 --> 07:47.429
WHEN HE TALKED ABOUT
THE ILLEGALS,

07:47.460 --> 07:49.599
YOU COULD TELL
HE RESPECTED THEM.

07:49.630 --> 07:51.598
HE COULD HAVE NEVER OPERATED
ON THEIR LEVEL,

07:51.630 --> 07:54.997
BUT IT WAS LIKE
HE HAD THIS RIVALRY
GOING ON WITH THEM --

07:55.040 --> 07:56.462
IN HIS HEAD.

07:56.510 --> 07:59.161
WELL, NINA NEVER HAD MUCH
ON THE ILLEGALS,

07:59.210 --> 08:01.599
BUT WHAT SHE DID KNOW,
SHE TOLD ME.

08:01.640 --> 08:03.141
YOU SURE?

08:04.550 --> 08:07.269
I MEAN, IT GOT SO I TRUSTED
MY GUY ON THE INSIDE SO MUCH,

08:07.320 --> 08:10.118
TILL I REALIZED HALF
OF WHAT HE SAID WAS BULLSHIT.

08:10.150 --> 08:11.447
[ SCOFFS ]

08:11.490 --> 08:13.515
HE THOUGHT
HE WAS RUNNING ME.

08:14.560 --> 08:16.312
THAT SOUNDS COMPLICATED.

08:17.330 --> 08:18.979
IT WAS.

08:20.860 --> 08:22.350
BUT YOU'RE LUCKY.

08:22.400 --> 08:25.665
YOU WERE WORKING
WITH A GOOD WOMAN.

08:28.340 --> 08:30.205
HEY, LOOK,
WHAT DO I KNOW?

08:30.240 --> 08:31.639
ANYTHING'S POSSIBLE.

08:31.670 --> 08:33.979
NINA COULD HAVE BEEN
A PATHOLOGICAL LIAR.

08:34.010 --> 08:36.308
SHE COULD HAVE SHOT J.R.,
FOR ALL I KNOW.

08:36.340 --> 08:38.149
[ CHUCKLES ]

08:38.180 --> 08:41.013
BUT I THINK
SHE WAS A GOOD SOURCE.

08:41.050 --> 08:43.348
WELL...

08:44.920 --> 08:47.388
IT'S REALLY TOO BAD,
WHAT HAPPENED.

08:52.930 --> 08:54.557
HEY.
HEY.

08:54.600 --> 08:56.568
HOW YOU DOING?
GOOD. YOU?

08:56.600 --> 08:58.727
I'M ALL RIGHT.
WHERE ARE YOU GOING?
ENGLISH CLASS.

08:58.770 --> 09:00.829
ENGLISH CLASS.
JUST GETTING OUT OF HISTORY.

09:00.870 --> 09:02.838
YEAH? HOW WAS IT?
YEAH, IT WAS ALL RIGHT.

09:02.870 --> 09:04.735
I WISH I WAS IN THERE NOW.
IT'S SO COLD.

09:04.770 --> 09:05.907
IT'S FREEZING.

09:07.440 --> 09:09.237
YOU THOUGHT
I WAS IMAGINING THINGS

09:09.280 --> 09:11.077
WHEN I FIRST TOLD YOU
ABOUT HIM.

09:12.050 --> 09:13.369
PEOPLE CAN GET OVEREAGER

09:13.420 --> 09:15.047
WHEN THEY START LEARNING
HOW TO DO THIS.

09:16.220 --> 09:18.745
A SOPHOMORE
AT GEORGE WASHINGTON --

09:18.790 --> 09:21.679
I SEE
WHY IT LOOKED SILLY.

09:21.720 --> 09:24.518
THEY PROBABLY RECRUITED TODD
BACK IN SOUTH AFRICA,

09:24.560 --> 09:26.187
WHEN THEY COULD
TAKE ADVANTAGE OF THE FACT

09:26.230 --> 09:27.595
THAT HE WAS
YOUNG AND NAIVE.

09:27.630 --> 09:30.019
HE WASN'T NAIVE.

09:30.070 --> 09:34.359
I GREW UP WITH SO MANY LIKE HIM
BACK IN JOHANNESBURG --

09:34.400 --> 09:36.868
PRIVILEGED, SELF-CENTERED,

09:36.910 --> 09:40.778
LITTLE, MINIATURE COPIES
OF THEIR PARENTS.

09:42.310 --> 09:43.902
I PHOTOGRAPHED HIM

09:43.950 --> 09:45.906
MEETING A SOUTH AFRICAN
INTELLIGENCE OFFICER --

09:45.950 --> 09:47.372
EUGENE VENTER.

09:47.420 --> 09:49.547
WE THINK HE'S PLANNING
TO STAGE AN ATTACK

09:49.580 --> 09:51.218
AND BLAME
THE STUDENT GROUPS HERE

09:51.250 --> 09:52.911
WHO ARE PROTESTING
APARTH EID.

09:54.420 --> 09:56.058
THAT'S REUBEN NCGOBO.

09:56.090 --> 09:58.923
WE THINK VENTER WON'T BE ABLE
TO RESIST COMING AFTER HIM

09:58.960 --> 10:00.552
ONCE HE KNOWS HE'S HERE.

10:00.600 --> 10:04.229
NCGOBO'S GOING TO SET
ANOTHER MEETING WITH TODD.

10:04.270 --> 10:07.398
WE'RE HOPING VENTER SHOWS UP
TO KILL NCGOBO.

10:07.440 --> 10:08.896
THAT'S WHEN WE GRAB HIM.

10:08.940 --> 10:10.737
HOW DO YOU KNOW
HE'LL GO FOR IT?

10:10.770 --> 10:13.409
WE DON'T. THERE'S
A GREATER CHANCE THAT HE WON'T.

10:13.440 --> 10:15.772
YOU ALWAYS PLAY AGAINST THE ODDS
IN THIS WORK.

10:15.810 --> 10:17.801
SO, WHAT DO I DO?

10:17.850 --> 10:20.444
OUR MAIN RISK
IS SQUAD CARS ON PATROL.

10:20.480 --> 10:22.914
WE'LL SET YOU IN A PLACE
WHERE YOU CAN SEE

10:22.950 --> 10:24.918
THE MAXIMUM NUMBER
OF CROSSROADS.

10:24.950 --> 10:29.250
IF YOU DO SEE A POLICE CAR,
HONK TWICE, SHORT TAPS.

10:29.290 --> 10:30.621
THEN PULL AWAY.

10:30.660 --> 10:33.299
I UNDERSTAND.

10:35.300 --> 10:36.597
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

10:36.630 --> 10:39.838
Philip:
HELLO! ANYBODY HUNGRY?

10:39.870 --> 10:41.838
GOT PIZZA.

10:41.870 --> 10:44.600
AND I DID HAVE THEM
PUT ON

10:44.640 --> 10:48.178
EXTRA PINEAPPLE,
ANCHOVIES, AND PICKLES.

10:51.480 --> 10:53.971
I ALREADY ATE.

10:55.980 --> 10:56.947
OKAY.

10:56.990 --> 10:59.618
UH, HENRY! PIZZA!

10:59.650 --> 11:02.824
HE'S AT DOUG'S,
WORKING ON HIS SCIENCE PROJECT.

11:07.660 --> 11:09.321
[ SIGHS ]

11:13.170 --> 11:16.037
I ASKED SANDRA
TO COME TO THE MEMORIAL.

11:16.070 --> 11:18.368
IT WAS STUPID OF ME.

11:18.410 --> 11:22.130
SHE'S GONNA FLY HALFWAY
ACROSS THE COUNTRY WITH ME NOW.

11:22.180 --> 11:24.808
SHE'S WITH
THIS OTHER GUY...

11:24.850 --> 11:26.977
MUST HAVE SEEMED
LIKE A TOTAL ASSHOLE.

11:27.020 --> 11:29.170
I DOUBT
SHE THOUGHT THAT.

11:31.020 --> 11:32.214
DON'T DOUBT IT.

11:35.190 --> 11:37.829
WORK'S GOOD,
OTH ERWISE?

11:37.860 --> 11:39.179
IT'S OKAY.

11:41.360 --> 11:44.397
THERE IS THIS ONE GUY.

11:44.430 --> 11:46.159
HE'S JUST --

11:46.200 --> 11:47.667
[ SIGHS ]

11:47.700 --> 11:50.009
HE ASKS
A LOT OF QUESTIONS.

11:50.040 --> 11:51.064
BUGS ME.

11:51.110 --> 11:52.532
WHY?

11:52.570 --> 11:54.504
HE'S A NEW GUY.

11:54.540 --> 11:57.703
HE'S ALWAYS TRYING
TO GET IN THERE, GET NOTICED.

11:57.750 --> 11:59.342
HE'S A BLACK GUY.

11:59.380 --> 12:03.009
HE'S GOOD AT WHAT HE DOES.
HE'S JUST TOO...

12:03.050 --> 12:05.416
I DON'T KNOW.

12:05.450 --> 12:08.010
WHAT ABOUT YOU?
WHAT'S HAPPENING IN YOUR HOUSE?

12:08.060 --> 12:10.358
KIDS ARE BUSY.
ELIZABETH'S BUSY.

12:10.390 --> 12:12.221
YOU KNOW.
I EAT PIZZA.

12:14.460 --> 12:17.725
HONESTLY, RAISING KIDS,
TRYING TO AGREE ON THINGS,

12:17.770 --> 12:20.864
LATELY...

12:20.900 --> 12:23.232
WE'RE ON OPPOSITE SIDES
ALL THE TIME.

12:28.910 --> 12:31.276
WELL, YOU'RE IN A BETTER PLACE
THAN ME, PAL.

12:31.310 --> 12:33.210
HANG IN THERE.

12:33.250 --> 12:35.070
[ SIGHS ]

12:35.120 --> 12:36.917
YEAH.

12:38.590 --> 12:40.114
YEAH.

12:41.660 --> 12:45.050
I WAS ON MY WAY HOME FROM MOSCOW
TO SEE MY WIFE AND KIDS,

12:45.090 --> 12:46.899
WHEN THEY TOLD ME
TO COME HERE.

12:46.930 --> 12:48.397
WHEN WERE YOU LAST HOME?

12:48.430 --> 12:50.569
A YEAR AND A HALF.

12:50.600 --> 12:53.296
BUT IT'S MORE THAN WORTH IT
IF WE GET VENTER.

12:53.340 --> 12:55.638
WE'LL GET YOU BACK SAFE.

12:55.670 --> 12:57.137
YOU HAVE KIDS?

13:00.180 --> 13:02.603
BOYS? GIRLS?

13:04.110 --> 13:06.078
I HAVE ONE OF EACH.

13:06.110 --> 13:08.271
ONE OF EACH.

13:08.320 --> 13:10.117
LUCKY MAMA.

13:12.450 --> 13:14.088
DO YOUR KIDS
HAVE ANY IDEA

13:14.120 --> 13:15.985
WHAT A BADASS WOMAN
THEIR MOM IS?

13:16.020 --> 13:17.988
[ CHUCKLES ]

13:18.030 --> 13:20.498
THEY THINK
I RUN A SMALL FAMILY BUSINESS.

13:20.530 --> 13:22.452
[ LAUGHS ]

13:25.300 --> 13:26.460
I HAVE FOUR BOYS.

13:26.500 --> 13:28.263
WHERE DO THEY THINK
YOU ARE?

13:28.300 --> 13:29.961
THEY KNOW NOT TO ASK.

13:32.670 --> 13:36.674
I AM AFRAID
OF WHAT THEY'VE BECOME.

13:36.710 --> 13:40.840
WHEN I LEFT, BUTH WAS OBSESSED
WITH MOTORBIKES --

13:40.880 --> 13:42.848
ANYTHING FAST AND SHINY.

13:42.890 --> 13:46.439
HE WOULD COLLECT
THESE PICTURES FROM MAGAZINES.

13:46.490 --> 13:50.950
I TELL HIM,
"YOU CARE ABOUT THIS

13:50.990 --> 13:54.357
WHEN WE LIVE LIKE DOGS
IN SHACKS, WITH NOTHING."

13:54.400 --> 13:56.288
NO MATTER
HOW MANY TIMES

13:56.330 --> 13:58.298
I RIPPED UP THE PICTURES
AND BEAT HIM,

13:58.330 --> 14:00.969
HE WOULD ALWAYS
FIND MORE.

14:01.000 --> 14:02.968
I KNOW.

14:03.010 --> 14:05.638
AMERICANS DON'T DISCIPLINE
THEIR KIDS THIS WAY.

14:05.670 --> 14:07.479
I'M NOT AMERICAN.

14:07.510 --> 14:09.137
HE'S A LITTLE GUY.

14:09.180 --> 14:11.045
IF HE HAD A MOTORBIKE,

14:11.080 --> 14:14.641
SOMEONE WOULD BEAT HIM,
KILL HIM FOR IT.

14:14.680 --> 14:17.888
I DON'T WANT HIM
TO GO THAT WAY.

14:17.920 --> 14:20.150
BETTER TO DIE FIGHTING

14:20.190 --> 14:24.229
FOR CITIZENSHIP,
FOR FREEDOM, YES?

14:24.260 --> 14:26.524
YES.

14:28.400 --> 14:30.664
YES, I'M CALLING TO CONFIRM

14:30.700 --> 14:34.488
ZINAIDA PREOBRAZHENSKAYA'S
APPOINTMENT TOMORROW.

14:34.540 --> 14:36.690
YEAH, I'LL HOLD.

14:51.550 --> 14:53.518
[ RECEIVER CLICKS IN CRADLE ]

14:53.560 --> 14:55.551
[ PAPERS RUSTLE ]

15:01.730 --> 15:03.220
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

15:03.270 --> 15:04.396
Gaad: YEAH?

15:04.430 --> 15:05.692
I NEED A SIGNATURE.

15:05.730 --> 15:08.369
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

15:08.400 --> 15:11.403
I WENT THROUGH FOUR FILES,
I READ EVERY SINGLE REPORT,

15:11.440 --> 15:12.907
AND AT THE END
OF THE DAY,

15:12.940 --> 15:15.033
UH, I-I DON'T THINK
THERE'S ANYTHING THERE.

15:15.080 --> 15:17.378
I MEAN, HE'S NOT INTERESTED
IN WORKING WITH THE AMERICANS,

15:17.410 --> 15:19.105
THE FRENCH, THE BRITISH,
OR THE AUSTRALIANS.

15:19.150 --> 15:20.708
TRUTH BE TOLD,
I JUST THINK

15:20.750 --> 15:22.718
HE WANTED TO GET AWAY
FROM HIS WIFE AND KIDS.

15:22.750 --> 15:24.081
[ PEN CAP RATTLES ]

15:28.490 --> 15:30.287
[ RATTLING ]

15:32.830 --> 15:36.129
[ RATTLING ]

16:30.990 --> 16:34.187
WELL, I THINK
THAT'S ENOUGH FOR NOW.

16:34.220 --> 16:36.279
WHY DON'T YOU TWO
GO BACK TO YOUR DESKS,

16:36.320 --> 16:39.323
AND I'LL, UH...
LET YOU KNOW.

17:12.190 --> 17:14.192
[ STALL DOOR LOCKS ]

17:50.970 --> 17:53.530
[ DOOR OPENS ]

17:53.570 --> 17:55.538
[ FOOTSTEPS APPROACH ]

17:55.570 --> 17:57.106
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

17:57.140 --> 17:59.233
[ STALL DOOR
OPENS, CLOSES, LOCKS ]

17:59.270 --> 18:02.535
[ FABRIC SLIDES ]

18:02.580 --> 18:04.741
[ URINATING ]

18:08.250 --> 18:10.445
[ URINATING STOPS ]

18:10.490 --> 18:13.459
[ TOILET PAPER DISPENSER
CLICKS ]

18:13.490 --> 18:16.880
[ TOILET FLUSHES ]

18:16.920 --> 18:18.956
[ FOOTSTEPS DEPART ]

18:21.160 --> 18:22.889
[ PAPER TOWEL RIPS ]

18:22.930 --> 18:24.568
[ TOWEL RUBBING ]

18:24.600 --> 18:26.295
[ FOOTSTEPS DEPART ]

18:28.940 --> 18:31.238
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

18:31.270 --> 18:33.431
[ EXHALES DEEPLY ]

19:03.140 --> 19:05.005
[ INHALES SHAKILY ]

19:05.040 --> 19:07.304
[ EXHALES DEEPLY ]

19:16.150 --> 19:18.186
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

19:29.030 --> 19:31.123
[ DETECTOR CLICKING ]

19:31.170 --> 19:33.991
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

20:57.080 --> 20:58.081
Gaad: MARTHA?

20:59.120 --> 21:01.259
THIS IS WALTER TAFFET,
FROM O.P.R.

21:01.290 --> 21:03.588
WOULD YOU COME WITH US,
PLEASE?

21:10.430 --> 21:12.398
GENE, WILL YOU EXCUSE US
FOR A MOMENT?

21:12.430 --> 21:14.261
UH, SURE.

21:26.480 --> 21:27.412
WHO'S THAT?

21:27.450 --> 21:29.247
OUR COMPUTER SPECIALIST.

21:29.280 --> 21:30.747
WHEN DID HE START?

21:30.790 --> 21:32.087
UH...

21:32.120 --> 21:33.485
LAST JANUARY.

21:33.520 --> 21:36.318
WELL, I'LL NEED TO TALK TO HIM,
FOR STARTERS.

21:38.130 --> 21:41.588
CAN YOU PROVIDE ME
WITH THE LOGS

21:41.630 --> 21:43.825
OF ALL
OF AGENT GAAD'S VISITORS?

21:43.870 --> 21:46.498
UH, HOW -- HOW FAR BACK
WOULD YOU LIKE ME TO GO?

21:46.530 --> 21:48.760
LET'S START
WITH THREE MONTHS.

21:48.800 --> 21:50.836
RIGHT AWAY, SIR.

21:56.010 --> 21:58.945
WELL, THE SWEEPERS
ARE GOING FLOOR TO FLOOR NOW.

21:58.980 --> 22:01.448
IF THEY DON'T FIND ANYTHING,
I'LL START INTERVIEWS TOMORROW.

22:01.480 --> 22:02.947
HOW LIKELY
DO YOU THINK IT IS

22:02.980 --> 22:05.289
THAT THIS IS COMING
FROM MY DEPARTMENT?

22:05.320 --> 22:08.289
THIS COULD BE A JANITOR
WHO GOT FIRED A YEAR AGO,

22:08.320 --> 22:10.527
COULD BE
ONE OF YOUR AGENTS...

22:10.560 --> 22:11.822
COULD BE YOU.

22:21.340 --> 22:23.661
YOU READY?

22:23.710 --> 22:25.200
YEAH.

22:35.750 --> 22:38.514
[ LAUGHTER ]

22:40.220 --> 22:42.154
SO, WHAT'S YOUR FAVORITE
KIND OF FOOD, LISA?

22:42.190 --> 22:44.181
OH,
I LIKE ALL KINDS.

22:44.230 --> 22:45.982
YOU EVER HAD SUSHI?

22:46.030 --> 22:47.019
NOT YET.

22:47.060 --> 22:48.698
JACK TOOK ME LAST WEEK.

22:48.730 --> 22:49.992
RAW FISH.

22:50.030 --> 22:51.224
Lisa: UGH.
I COULDN'T HANDLE IT.

22:51.270 --> 22:53.067
OH, I LOVE IT.

22:53.100 --> 22:55.068
[ LAUGHTER ]

22:55.100 --> 22:57.898
ON OUR FIRST DATE, HE TOOK ME
TO THIS FRENCH BISTRO.

22:57.940 --> 22:59.066
AWW.

22:59.110 --> 23:01.908
THAT WAS --
IT WAS SO FUN.

23:01.940 --> 23:03.874
IT WAS.

23:08.780 --> 23:10.213
[ LAUGHS ]

23:10.250 --> 23:12.047
SO, JACK...

23:12.090 --> 23:13.409
SO, LISA...

23:13.460 --> 23:15.212
[ LAUGHING ]

23:15.260 --> 23:16.511
TELL ME ABOUT YOURSELF.

23:16.560 --> 23:18.528
WHAT DO YOU WANT TO KNOW?

23:18.560 --> 23:20.528
UH, I DON'T KNOW --
THE USUAL.

23:20.560 --> 23:22.528
WHERE ARE YOU FROM?
YOUR JOB?

23:22.560 --> 23:24.869
IS THAT REALLY WHAT YOU WANT
TO KNOW, OR DO YOU WANT TO KNOW

23:24.900 --> 23:26.527
IF I'M GOOD ENOUGH
FOR MICHELLE, HERE?

23:26.570 --> 23:28.561
[ LAUGHS ]

23:28.600 --> 23:31.034
NO, I'M JUST ASKING.
IT'S OKAY,
IT'S OKAY, IT'S OKAY.

23:31.070 --> 23:32.935
YOU KNOW, I LIKE THE FACT
YOU'RE LOOKING OUT FOR HER.

23:32.970 --> 23:35.029
OKAY.
[ INHALES DEEPLY ]
[ LAUGHS ]

23:35.080 --> 23:37.548
I HAVE BEEN MARRIED BEFORE --
A LONG TIME AGO,

23:37.580 --> 23:39.605
WHEN I WAS YOUNG
AND A REAL KNUCKLEHEAD.

23:39.650 --> 23:40.719
NO KIDS.

23:40.750 --> 23:42.377
UM...

23:42.420 --> 23:44.945
I'VE HAD THE SAME JOB,
WHICH I LOVE,

23:44.990 --> 23:47.379
FOR GOING ON 15 YEARS,

23:47.420 --> 23:50.958
AND I THINK
MEETING MICHELLE, HERE,

23:50.990 --> 23:53.379
IS PROBABLY
ONE OF THE BEST THINGS

23:53.430 --> 23:55.421
THAT'S HAPPENED TO ME
IN A VERY LONG TIME.

23:58.670 --> 24:00.638
WOULD YOU AGREE?

24:00.670 --> 24:02.433
I WOULD.

24:04.270 --> 24:05.567
ANYTHING ELSE?

24:05.610 --> 24:07.066
[ CHUCKLES ]
NOT RIGHT NOW.

24:07.110 --> 24:08.975
GOOD,
'CAUSE I'M STARVING.

24:09.010 --> 24:10.978
YOU EVER HAD
A VEAL MILANESE?

24:11.010 --> 24:12.272
UH, NO.
[ LAUGHS ]

24:12.310 --> 24:13.402
YOU'RE GONNA LOVE IT.

24:13.450 --> 24:14.940
OKAY. [ LAUGHS ]

24:36.840 --> 24:39.308
[ BREATHING SHAKILY ]

24:42.640 --> 24:44.801
[ SNIFFLES ]

25:04.830 --> 25:06.821
[ SIGHS ]

25:19.750 --> 25:21.672
[ SNIFFLES ]

25:57.790 --> 26:00.588
I'M GONNA GO TO MARTHA'S
TONIGHT.

26:08.060 --> 26:09.698
SEE YOU TOMORROW, THEN.

26:09.730 --> 26:11.061
MM-HMM.

26:16.240 --> 26:19.368
MAYBE VENTER
WON'T EVEN SHOW UP.

26:19.410 --> 26:21.435
MAYBE NOT.

26:21.480 --> 26:25.598
IF HE DOES, I WISH I HAD
A FEW MORE MONTHS WITH HANS.

26:25.650 --> 26:27.777
AS LONG AS WE KEEP HIM
FAR ENOUGH BACK,

26:27.820 --> 26:29.617
WE SHOULD BE FINE.

26:31.420 --> 26:35.208
NCGOBO WAS
TALKING ABOUT HIS SONS.

26:35.260 --> 26:37.558
HE HAS FOUR OF THEM.

26:37.590 --> 26:41.219
HE SAID HE HOPES THEY ALL BECOME
FIGHTERS, LIKE HIM.

26:41.260 --> 26:44.388
AND YOU THINK
THAT'S A GOOD THING?

26:44.430 --> 26:46.261
WHAT?

26:48.940 --> 26:52.637
I FELT FOR HIM
AND HIS KIDS,

26:52.670 --> 26:57.130
FIGHTING
THIS BRUTAL, HORRENDOUS WAR.

26:57.180 --> 26:59.899
I MEAN, IT'S HORRIBLE,

26:59.950 --> 27:03.272
BUT IT'S...ADMIRABLE
IN A WAY.

27:03.320 --> 27:05.242
IT'S BRAVE.

27:05.290 --> 27:07.952
THEY DON'T HAVE
A LOT OF CHOICES.

27:09.620 --> 27:11.281
[ SIGHS ]

27:12.790 --> 27:14.951
NO. THEY DON'T.

27:17.300 --> 27:19.621
I HAVE TO GO.

27:21.970 --> 27:24.131
[ ENGINE TURNS OVER ]

27:26.310 --> 27:28.107
[ SIGHS ]

27:46.330 --> 27:48.491
[ CAR DOORS CLOSE ]

27:52.730 --> 27:54.288
[ DOOR OPENS ]

27:54.340 --> 27:56.137
HEY.
HEY.

27:56.170 --> 27:58.809
UH, I'M GONNA PUT THIS UPSTAIRS
AND DO SOME HOMEWORK.

27:58.840 --> 27:59.829
BYE, MOM.

28:10.180 --> 28:11.317
HI.

28:11.350 --> 28:14.012
HEY.

28:14.060 --> 28:15.982
UH, HOW ARE YOU?
ARE YOU OKAY?

28:16.020 --> 28:17.510
YEAH, SURE.

28:17.560 --> 28:18.822
CRAP AT WORK, YOU KNOW.

28:18.860 --> 28:20.327
I-I-I TALKED TO ARTHUR.

28:20.360 --> 28:23.056
OH. I'M SORRY I EVEN ASKED YOU
TO COME WITH ME.

28:23.100 --> 28:25.159
I DON'T KNOW
WHAT I WAS THINKING.

28:25.200 --> 28:27.896
NO, I -- A PART OF ME WANTED
TO GO, YOU KNOW, OF COURSE,

28:27.940 --> 28:32.229
BUT I'M NOT YOUR WIFE
ANYMORE, SO...

28:34.380 --> 28:37.008
YOU'RE STILL MY WIFE.

28:37.040 --> 28:38.905
TECHNICALLY SPEAKING.

28:42.220 --> 28:44.211
YEAH.

28:44.250 --> 28:45.387
YEAH.

28:45.420 --> 28:48.355
UH...

28:48.390 --> 28:50.688
[ SIGHS ]

28:50.720 --> 28:54.019
I THINK
IT'S TIME THAT WE...

28:54.060 --> 28:55.721
DID SOMETHING ABOUT THAT.

29:09.980 --> 29:11.379
[ DOOR OPENS ]

29:11.410 --> 29:12.775
HI, HONEY.

29:14.820 --> 29:16.048
HOW ARE YOU?

29:16.080 --> 29:18.287
IN -- IN HERE.

29:20.250 --> 29:22.081
GOOD TO SEE YOU.

29:24.160 --> 29:25.127
HEY.

29:25.160 --> 29:26.752
HEY.

29:28.930 --> 29:30.557
SOMETHING WRONG?

29:30.600 --> 29:31.897
NO. NO.

29:31.930 --> 29:34.398
UM, JUST -- I'M --
I'M -- I'M TIRED.

29:34.440 --> 29:36.135
LONG DAY.

29:36.170 --> 29:38.263
[ SNIFFLES ]

29:45.610 --> 29:49.740
I, UH, I HAVE A...EARLY FLIGHT
TO, UM, INDIANAPOLIS...

29:49.780 --> 29:51.316
MM-HMM?
...TOMORROW MORNING,

29:51.350 --> 29:54.251
BUT I'M GLAD WE --
WE GET A NIGHT TOGETHER.

29:54.290 --> 29:57.612
WHERE'S YOUR PURSE?

29:59.960 --> 30:02.451
YOU KNOW,
I LEFT IT AT WORK.

30:04.130 --> 30:05.620
WHAT?

30:09.140 --> 30:10.596
WHERE?

30:10.640 --> 30:13.006
UH, IT'S IN MY DESK DRAWER,
SO DON'T WORRY.

30:13.040 --> 30:14.177
NO ONE CAN TOUCH IT.

30:14.210 --> 30:15.609
I...

30:15.640 --> 30:18.768
I, UM, I JUST FORGOT IT,
LIKE A TOTAL DITZ.

30:18.810 --> 30:22.268
I, UH, WENT SHOPPING
AT LUNCHTIME, AND I HAD BAGS,

30:22.320 --> 30:24.117
AND THEN, WHEN I LEFT,
I FORGOT THE PURSE,

30:24.150 --> 30:27.984
AND I HAD TO GET THE SPARE KEY
FROM DIANE.

30:30.160 --> 30:32.628
WELL,
I'M GLAD SHE WAS HOME.

30:34.860 --> 30:37.158
OH. UH...

30:37.200 --> 30:39.521
BORING, UNEVENTFUL --
FINE.

30:42.170 --> 30:44.138
YOU KNOW
WHAT I WAS THINKING?

30:44.170 --> 30:46.866
I HAVE NEVER
BEEN TO YOUR APARTMENT.

30:49.040 --> 30:51.372
LET'S PICK A NIGHT.

30:51.410 --> 30:53.640
WE CAN ORDER TAKEOUT

30:53.680 --> 30:56.979
AND DINE BY CANDLELIGHT
AT MY VERY SMALL TABLE.

30:57.020 --> 31:02.481
WE COULD EVEN, MAYBE,
TRY A NEW POSITION ON THE FUTON.

31:02.520 --> 31:04.226
SOUNDS NICE.

31:06.360 --> 31:09.852
HOW ABOUT...
WE GO THERE TONIGHT?

31:12.030 --> 31:13.998
...INVITED THE PRIME MINISTER
TO JOIN ME TOMORROW

31:14.040 --> 31:16.838
FOR BREAKFAST SO THAT WE CAN
DISCUSS IN MORE DETAIL

31:16.870 --> 31:19.009
THE EFFORTS
THAT BOTH OF US ARE MAKING

31:19.040 --> 31:21.008
TO SECURE
A MORE PEACEFUL WORLD.

31:21.040 --> 31:25.249
SO OUR STATEMENTS, AS A RESULT
OF ALL OF OUR DISCUSSIONS,

31:25.280 --> 31:28.511
WILL BE MADE TOMORROW MORNING,
FOLLOWING THAT BREAKFAST

31:28.550 --> 31:31.018
AND BEFORE
THE PRIME MINISTER'S DEPARTURE.
IS THERE
ANYTHING TO EAT?

31:31.050 --> 31:32.187
OH. UH...

31:32.220 --> 31:34.085
[ TV TURNS OFF ]
YEAH.

31:34.120 --> 31:36.088
YEAH,
I PICKED UP SOME THINGS.

31:36.120 --> 31:39.851
LET'S SEE -- I GOT, UH,
SOME BOLOGNA AND A FROZEN PIZZA,

31:39.890 --> 31:43.223
AND I ALSO HAVE THIS.

31:46.300 --> 31:48.029
JUST ADD HEAT.

31:48.070 --> 31:49.537
MANAGEABLE.

31:49.570 --> 31:51.731
OKAY.

31:57.740 --> 32:00.402
[ SIGHS ]

32:14.260 --> 32:16.228
SO, UH...

32:16.260 --> 32:18.262
ARE YOU GOING
TO THAT FUNERAL IN CHICAGO?

32:19.270 --> 32:21.090
UH, YEAH.

32:21.140 --> 32:23.392
YEAH, IT'S A MEMORIAL,
ACTUALLY.

32:23.440 --> 32:27.763
LOT OF AGENTS
ARE GONNA BE THERE.

32:27.810 --> 32:31.246
YOU KNOW, DAVE AND I
WORKED UNDERCOVER TOGETHER.

32:31.280 --> 32:32.747
DID YOU KNOW THAT?

32:32.780 --> 32:34.111
NO.

32:34.150 --> 32:36.914
NO, I THOUGHT
YOU GUYS WERE JUST FRIENDS.

32:36.950 --> 32:38.281
YEAH.

32:39.690 --> 32:42.158
HE WAS THE ONLY PERSON
I COULD TALK TO ABOUT THAT

32:42.190 --> 32:44.579
FOR A...

32:44.630 --> 32:46.655
A LONG TIME.

32:49.130 --> 32:50.950
WHAT WAS IT LIKE?

32:52.830 --> 32:54.639
IT WAS STRANGE.

32:55.800 --> 32:58.268
HARD.

32:58.310 --> 33:00.301
I...

33:03.640 --> 33:05.141
YOU KNOW...

33:08.220 --> 33:10.279
I GOT PRETTY SCREWED UP.

33:10.320 --> 33:11.981
HOW SO?

33:12.020 --> 33:14.955
I HAD TO PRETEND
TO BE FRIENDS WITH PEOPLE

33:14.990 --> 33:17.618
I REALLY DIDN'T LIKE --

33:21.330 --> 33:24.663
THERE WAS A MAN --
JOHN REISLING.

33:26.500 --> 33:29.333
HE'S IN SAN QUENTIN NOW.

33:32.370 --> 33:34.634
HE WAS A BAD GUY.

33:34.680 --> 33:36.500
UH, WHAT DID HE DO?

33:42.020 --> 33:44.386
BAD THINGS.

33:44.420 --> 33:45.978
LIKE WHAT?

33:46.020 --> 33:47.840
DID HE KILL PEOPLE?

33:49.190 --> 33:51.010
HE DID.

33:57.230 --> 34:00.028
IT'S OKAY.
YOU CAN ASK ME.

34:02.770 --> 34:04.829
DID HE MAKE YOU
KILL PEOPLE?

34:04.870 --> 34:06.531
NO.

34:08.540 --> 34:10.906
NO. THANK GOD.

34:14.280 --> 34:15.872
WERE YOU SCARED?

34:37.440 --> 34:42.707
SO, I KNOW I HAVE
SOME CANDLES IN HERE,

34:42.740 --> 34:44.879
AND, UH...

34:44.910 --> 34:46.946
TAKEOUT MENU.

34:52.250 --> 34:54.787
YOU KNOW, I WAS, UH...

34:54.820 --> 34:57.118
I WAS SAVING THIS
FOR OUR ANNIVERSARY,

34:57.160 --> 34:59.424
BUT WE COULD HAVE IT
TONIGHT.

35:02.600 --> 35:05.763
YEAH, I KNOW.
IT JUST NEEDS A WOMAN'S TOUCH.

35:08.270 --> 35:09.430
CLARK.

35:09.470 --> 35:10.596
MM-HMM?

35:10.640 --> 35:12.130
[ SIGHS ]

35:12.170 --> 35:14.900
DO YOU THINK THAT WE'RE EVER
GONNA LIVE TOGETHER,

35:14.940 --> 35:16.737
LIKE A NORMAL
MARRIED COUPLE?

35:16.780 --> 35:18.407
[ SIGHS ]

35:18.450 --> 35:22.409
MARTHA,
I DON'T HAVE A NORMAL LIFE.

35:22.450 --> 35:25.089
I DON'T HAVE
A NORMAL JOB.

35:25.120 --> 35:28.089
BUT THERE'S NOTHING SO GREAT
ABOUT NORMAL.

35:28.120 --> 35:29.917
OH, ISN'T THERE?

35:29.960 --> 35:32.758
NOR-- NORMAL IS
FOR EVERYBODY ELSE.

35:32.790 --> 35:36.419
BECAUSE...
IF YOU'RE ASKING ME

35:36.460 --> 35:38.792
DO I THINK
THINGS WILL GET BETTER,

35:38.830 --> 35:41.094
THEN THE ANSWER
IS "YES."

35:41.130 --> 35:43.337
AND WHEN I THINK
ABOUT US,

35:43.370 --> 35:47.261
I THINK IT KEEPS GETTING
BETTER AND BETTER.

35:47.310 --> 35:49.801
DON'T YOU?

35:53.980 --> 35:58.280
Y-- I-- I'M NOT REALLY
IN THE MOOD FOR THAT.

35:58.320 --> 35:59.514
LET'S SAVE IT.

36:01.660 --> 36:03.958
ARE YOU SURE?

36:03.990 --> 36:05.457
IS EVERYTHING OKAY?

36:05.490 --> 36:07.526
YEAH. YEAH.

36:16.570 --> 36:18.333
COME HERE.

36:40.560 --> 36:41.822
MM.

36:41.860 --> 36:43.498
UM...

36:43.530 --> 36:45.828
SORRY. I'M...

36:45.870 --> 36:46.996
MARTHA, WHAT'S WRONG?

36:47.030 --> 36:48.338
WANT TO TALK ABOUT IT?

36:48.370 --> 36:49.667
NO.
NO, NO, NO, NO, NO.

36:49.700 --> 36:52.066
I'M JUST, UH,
I'M JUST OFF TONIGHT.

36:52.110 --> 36:53.168
I...

36:53.210 --> 36:54.837
I SHOULD JUST GO TO BED.

36:54.880 --> 36:58.008
I'M -- I MIGHT BE
COMING DOWN WITH SOMETHING.

36:58.040 --> 36:59.507
YEAH.

36:59.550 --> 37:02.041
YEAH, THERE -- WELL,
THERE'S SOMETHING GOING AROUND.

37:03.880 --> 37:07.043
I THINK I, UH,
I WANT TO GO HOME.

37:07.090 --> 37:09.354
ARE YOU SURE?

37:09.390 --> 37:10.914
YEAH.

37:13.890 --> 37:16.222
OKAY. I'LL DRIVE YOU.

37:29.410 --> 37:30.570
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

38:15.960 --> 38:17.484
MM.

38:26.830 --> 38:28.661
[ SIGHS ]

38:28.700 --> 38:31.168
What time is it?

38:31.200 --> 38:33.134
It's late.

38:35.010 --> 38:37.137
[ BOTH SIGH ]

38:47.020 --> 38:50.512
I should have told you
about my talk with Paige.

39:06.710 --> 39:09.008
I HAVE A SON.

39:11.180 --> 39:13.341
ANOTHER SON.

39:16.520 --> 39:20.183
HE'S IRINA'S,
FROM WHEN WE WERE KIDS.

39:23.860 --> 39:25.885
20 YEARS OLD.

39:27.690 --> 39:31.399
AND HE'S IN AFGHANISTAN.

39:31.430 --> 39:33.523
GABRIEL TOLD ME.

40:01.230 --> 40:03.551
HE'S IN COMBAT?

40:06.730 --> 40:08.891
HE'S A PARATROOPER.

40:31.760 --> 40:33.227
HENRY,
DON'T FORGET YOUR POEM.

40:33.260 --> 40:35.228
HOW COULD I FORGET?
YOU TOLD ME 10 TIMES ALREADY.

40:35.260 --> 40:36.420
HENRY!

40:36.460 --> 40:38.052
WELL, I'M NOT READING IT
OUT LOUD.

40:38.100 --> 40:39.465
MRS. MaCELHANEY SAID THAT
YOU COULD READ YOUR OWN ALOUD

40:39.500 --> 40:41.559
OR YOU COULD TRADE
WITH A FRIEND.

40:41.600 --> 40:43.591
I DON'T WANT A FRIEND TO READ
MY POEM OUT LOUD. THAT'S WORSE.

40:43.640 --> 40:45.608
THEN YOU'RE NOT FOLLOWING
THE ASSIGNMENT.

40:45.640 --> 40:47.631
YOU'RE NOT A PART
OF THIS DISCOURSE, PAIGE.

40:47.670 --> 40:49.638
DISCOURSE?
THAT'S A GOOD WORD,
HENRY.

40:49.680 --> 40:51.773
HENRY, BOOK.

40:53.950 --> 40:55.747
THERE YOU GO.
THANKS.

40:55.780 --> 40:57.247
Paige:
WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?
I WAS TALKING TO DAD.

40:57.280 --> 40:58.918
BYE, GUYS.
BYE.

40:58.950 --> 41:00.781
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

41:06.130 --> 41:07.757
[ SIGHS ]

41:07.790 --> 41:10.122
SOMETHING'S UP
WITH MARTHA.

41:11.700 --> 41:14.464
I DON'T KNOW.
COULD BE THE FOSTER KID.

41:15.540 --> 41:18.100
SHE'S STILL ON THAT.

41:18.140 --> 41:19.801
WHAT ARE YOU GONNA DO?

41:19.840 --> 41:22.001
[ SIGHS ]
I DON'T KNOW.

